tags.description: Bayview Park is a hidden gem on Coronado Island. It has one of the best views of the San Diego Skyline. The view looks out across San Diego Bay from a gap between mansions on the north side of the island.
tags.name: Bayview Park

tags.description: On May 18, 2001, the City of Coronado dedicated its newly constructed world-class skatepark. Encompassing approximately 16,000 square feet of concrete ramps, bowls, grinds and jumps, the park is an artistic sculpture that caters to all levels of skill.
tags.name: Coronado Skatepark
